;; tsugite 継ぎ手 — seed peoples-continuity graph (real, PUBLIC, AGGREGATE human collectives only)
;; ADR-2606073800 · vocabulary: peoples-ontology (00-contracts/schemas/peoples-ontology.kotoba.edn)
;;
;; SCOPE GUARD (constitutional, G1 — read first):
;;   - tsugite is a PEOPLES-CONTINUITY map at AGGREGATE / collective scale, NEVER a person-tracking
;;     / individual-locator / border-enforcement / deportation / surveillance aid. NO individual
;;     records, NO real-time location, NO biometric appear here. Every :people node is a
;;     COLLECTIVE (:people/scope :aggregate).
;;   - The lens is DISPLACEMENT + ERASURE pressure vs PROTECTION, routed to CONTINUITY (継承).
;;     The 取-holder is the pressure; the bearer is the collective/tongue. karma lives ONLY on
;;     edges (:en/peril-load; N1). It routes to refuge + revitalization, never to interdiction.
;;
;; SOURCING: UNHCR/IOM aggregate displacement figures, UNESCO Atlas / Ethnologue EGIDS language
;;   vitality, and the existence of public protection instruments (1951/1961 Conventions) and
;;   named public revitalization programs (Kōhanga Reo, Pūnana Leo) are :authoritative; the
;;   SAMPLE is a bounded illustrative seed (:representative coverage), NOT exhaustive, and
;;   peril-load values are representative severities, NOT individual data. No fabricated
;;   coverage. Live aggregate ingest is G7/Council-gated. Vitality/status facts are DISCLOSED,
;;   never tsugite adjudications (N3).

